OL,3,CThe Welsh veteran who paved the way
OL,4,Cfor the allied advance after D-Day
OL,6,FAfter storming the beaches on D-Day,
OL,7,Fthe Allies' next challenge was
OL,8,Fsupplying reinforcements and equipment
OL,9,Ffor their advance into occupied Europe.
OL,11,FTo do this, they constructed vast
OL,12,Fartificial ports known as 'Mulberry
OL,13,Fharbours' and Richard Pelzer, from
OL,14,FSwansea, helped build them.
OL,16,FMr Pelzer, now 100 years old, served
OL,17,Fin the Royal Engineers throughout the
OL,18,Fwar.
