OL,3,CThe Welsh veteran who paved the way
OL,4,Cfor the allied advance after D-Day
OL,6,FBorn in Llansamlet near Swansea, he
OL,7,Fwas nineteen when he was called up to
OL,8,Ffight in World War Two.
OL,10,FAfter basic training, Richard
OL,11,Funderwent engineering training,
OL,12,Fworking on underwater demolitions.
OL,14,FOn D-Day itself, he and his comrades
OL,15,Flanded on Juno beach and immediately
OL,16,Ffaced the dangerous task of clearing
OL,17,Fthe landing beaches of booby traps so
OL,18,Fthe rest of the troops could make
OL,19,Ftheir way through.
