OL,3,CThe Welsh veteran who paved the way
OL,4,Cfor the allied advance after D-Day
OL,6,FRichard and his comrades had spend
OL,7,Fmany weeks before the invasion
OL,8,Fsecretly building the harbours in
OL,9,FScotland.
OL,11,FBut the next mammoth task saw hundreds
OL,12,Fof the prefabricated structures
OL,13,Fbrought across the Channel. The
OL,14,Fresulting ports, assembled in just 12
OL,15,Fdays by thousands of engineers,
OL,16,Ffeatured 6 miles of steel roadways.
OL,18,FIt was a pleasing moment, Richard
OL,19,Fsaid: "To say I was there when the
OL,20,Fkeel of that thing went down to the
OL,21,Fcompletion - I was a very lucky chap."
