OL,3,CThe Welsh veteran who paved the way
OL,4,Cfor the allied advance after D-Day
OL,6,FThe harbour which Richard helped build
OL,7,Fbecame known as Port Winston, allowing
OL,8,Ftwo-and-a-half million men and half a
OL,9,Fmillion vehicles to join the fighting.
OL,10,FIt was an engineering feat which sped
OL,11,Fup the end of the war.
OL,13,F"It was still operating in November of
OL,14,Fthat year - built in June and still
OL,15,Foperating. The people who built the
OL,16,FMulberry harbour knew that an army
OL,17,Fmarches on its stomach. To be honest,
OL,18,Fwithout Mulberry Harbour the invasion
OL,19,Fwould've flopped", said Richard.
